AFTER being
accused of being homophobic hip hop star Cassper Nyovest took to twitter to
explain that the accusations are not true and that he is doesn’t hate anyone. “I
love everybody, I don’t have a problem with gay or bi-sexual people”. He said
in the video that he has performed at gay pride in support of the LGBTIQ
community. “These allegations date back a few years ago when I twitted some,
which I meant as a joke and I’m sorry if I hurt anyone,” he said. The star who recently signed a partnership with Universal Music will soon host his next fill up event in December. His next album is also set to be on the way and will be released on the day of the event. 